<br>
I think that they are actually fairly well balanced, I may get shot for saying this on the monk boards, but I do feel that monks should be below Warriors in terms of defensive skills. Although I think that a better answer would be to adjust the class that's having the problem (warriors) as opposed to changing Monks who have settled into their nitch.<br>
<br>
An example of this MIGHT be to raise the Warrior Softcap from 1250ac to maybe 1400ac vs lowering Monks softcap from 1250ac to 1050ac. This as well as increasing maybe the length of hate from Taunt and increasing the actual hate from taunt .. MIGHT b a better solution imho. <br>
<br>
As far as AA skills for monks ... I think that some of the class AA skills for monks are fairly useless ... maybe an increase to skeak (either in terms of %) or better .. some way we could b better at CR / sneaking .. similar to the Ninja theory ... or even some form of Dim Mak (death touch) ... the martial art not the actual name .. such that it could take effect like certain posions.<br>
<br>
Other then more interesting AA class skills I think monks are fairly well balanced in terms of Def / Atk position ... as I mentionsed b4, Monks, Rogues and Warriors are PURE melee and as such should each have a def/atk &gt; hybrids, imho. Such that ...<br>
<br>
1 - Wars take damage best (best Def)<br>
2 - Rogues give damage best (best Off)<br>
3 - Monks are below Wars in Def, Monks are below Rogs in Atk<br>
4 - all Hybrids are below pure Melee in Atk/Def<br>
5 - Pallys and Sks are better at Def then other Hybrids<br>
6 - Rangers are better at atk then other melee<br>
7 - Bards are a tuff call ... would say above rangers, below Pally Sks in def, and below all in atk (hard call on bards)<br>
<br>
Obviously this is a personal viewpoint from playing the game since using Dorians Beta account ... and playing 3+ yrs. 8-) <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45917" TARGET=_blank> <IMG SRC="http://members.cox.net/gstg/ironsig.gif" BORDER=0> </A>

