You're right, the Vulak drops aren't strickly fair, in as much as very few guilds work that ring.  However, even if we pull those 3 drops from consideration, I believe the rest of the items clearly show the tendency.  And I believe I could come up with drops from one of the other boss mobs that wouldn't be quite as good but would still be very good for those 3 we remove.<br>
<br>
NToV respawns on a 3 day cycle as I recall.  Which means without server resets or zone crashes you have 10 shots at the boss mobs a month.  In three months you have 30 shots.  Even if you're sharing NToV, thats a fair number of drops in three months.  And some guilds have been farming NToV for a year or more.<br>
<br>
You say that the Warrior drops can be farmed easier?  I agree.  However, once the Warrior/Paladin/Shadow Knights are outfitted in quested, what else in the way of upgrades for those slots drop in NToV?  I believe there are what, two Breastplates, Breastplate of superiority and Breastplate of Fiery Might, neither of which could be considered a substantial upgrade to the Warlord Breastplate.  Basically there are NO Warrior/Paladin/Shadow Knight only upgrades for those slots in NToV from the boss mobs.  Some of the all/all pieces would be slight upgrades but most are fairly equal to Warlords.  Which means that Monks (also Rangers and Rogues, but thats a different issue) are being outfitted in armor that is equal to Warlords.  Doesn't that strike you as messed up?  Monks being outfitted in armor that is almost identical, where it isn't better, than Warrior armor?<br>
<br>
Once you get out of NToV and move on to Luclin, this changes somewhat.  But the damage has been pretty well done by then.<br>
<br>
So feel free to tell me that the Warriors can be outfitted easier because their drops don't come off the boss mobs.  You're right.  But when they do move onto the boss mobs, where are the better pieces for Warriors?  Why should the Warrior quested legs be 45 ac and the ancient wyvern hide legs be 46 ac?  Where is the sense in that?  In Kunark what was the highest tunic a Monk could get?  15 AC?  And a cobalt BP was 45 AC wasn't it?  My how the world has changed.<br>
