<br>
Offense~<br>
<br>
First off Monks have the best melee damage from the front, period. This isn't even disputable. Rogues have the best melee from behind. Rangers 'melee' ability is comparable to a warriors depending on what weapons the ranger and warrior are using - and whether or not the warrior is tanking. <br>
<br>
Ranger's ability to use archery is not even melee, its entirely different. As of right now archery is barely viable in high end encounters, and is only used by Rangers in my guild probably 30% of the time or so. So for perhaps 30% of the time Rangers are top damage dealers - and thats basically no 'boss' type mobs, unless its a rooted boss. <br>
<br>
SKs/Paladins are considerably farther behind monks - if you want to switch to an SK because they will be so much leeter than monks now...go for it. <br>
<br>
Defense<br>
Yeah SKs will be able to mitigate damage better, but hell shouldnt they? monks will still be able to avoid hits better though...I seriously doubt we see SKs becoming the main pullers if that's what you are so worried about.<br>
<br>
Rangers defense &gt; Monks? Well monks mitigation is being lowered and its rumored that Rangers defense is being raised to 240 on test, but i still doubt Rangers will tank better than Monks. As it stands, Chain classes should get hit for less than leather classes but chain classes should get hit more often. I imagine monks will still tank better than Rangers and Rogues - but that is yet to be seen BECAUSE IT ISN'T LIVE YET.<br>
<br>
And also for the most part, Rangers and Monks hitpoint differences are negligible.<br>
<br>
Pulling...<br>
<br>
Is this going to make a huge difference? Hell Necro's can pull Vex Thal now as it is...<br>
